==Dutch==
[[Category:Dutch personal pronouns]]
===Etymology===
Old Low Franconian [[gi]], from common Germanic ''*ji(z)'', ''*ju(z)''.  Near cognates include English [[ye]], German [[ihr]] "you" {{p}}, and Gothic [[𐌾𐌿𐍃]] (jus) "you" {{p}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/jɛi/}}, {{SAMPA|/jEi/}}

===Personal pronoun===
'''jij'''

# ''Second-person singular, subjective:'' [[you]].
#: ''Ben je daar?'' &mdash; Are you there?

